# GameNative — Library Adapter & Fragment

Map all type names to whatever already exists in the codebase.
"AppListAdapter" may be your current adapter class name or a new one.
"AppListFragment" / "LibraryScreen" / "LibraryListPane" — use the real name.

---

## Part 1 — Why the old adapter is slow

The stock adapter calls `notifyDataSetChanged()` which causes RecyclerView to
throw away and rebind every single card in the list — even if only one game's
download progress ticked up by 1%. On a library of 200 games, that is 200
image loads, 200 text redraws, and 200 chip color evaluations per second
while a game is downloading. This causes visible jank.

The fix is two-layered:
- **DiffUtil** compares the old and new list and only calls `onBindViewHolder`
  for the items that actually changed.
- **Payload updates** let a changed item update only the specific view that
  needs it (e.g. the progress bar) without re-loading the cover art via Coil.

---

## Part 2 — AppInfo data model

Add any missing fields to your existing app/game data class.
It must be a `data class` so `==` comparison works correctly with DiffUtil.

```kotlin
data class AppInfo(
    val appId: Int,
    val name: String,
    val capsuleImageUrl: String?,      // 600×900 portrait — for grid cards
    val iconImageUrl: String?,         // 32×32 icon — for list rows
    val installState: InstallState,
    val downloadProgress: Int,         // 0–100
    val isFavorite: Boolean,
    val sizeOnDisk: String?,           // e.g. "12.4 GB"
    val lastPlayedFormatted: String?   // e.g. "Yesterday" or "2.3 hrs"
)
```

The capsule image URL pattern:
```
https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steam/apps/{appId}/library_600x900.jpg
```
This is a different URL from the header image (`header.jpg`). The header is
460×215 landscape and looks broken in a 2:3 portrait card. Always use the
600×900 portrait capsule for grid cards.

